fields.description:

fields.summary: Windows: Compler warnings PRI249: 0xdef00520 - Invalid qualifier

comments.body: It turns out this happens only when ES6 transpile is set to {{true}}. The warning happens because Visual Studio incorrectly interpret some JavaScript files as i18 resources, just because it has minus sign ({{-}}) in the middle of the file name! OMG :(
FR Passed. Waiting on master Jenkins build.
